<article xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
  <info>
    <title>CiteProc Test</title>
  </info>
  <section>
    <info>
      <title>Introduction</title>
    </info>
    <para>CiteProc supports the following features, depending on the details of the style as
      specified in the <acronym>CSL</acronym> file: <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>Reference grouping and sorting <citation>
              <biblioref linkend="Tilly2000a"/>
              <biblioref linkend="Thrift1990a"/>
              <biblioref linkend="Tilly2002a"/>
            </citation>
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Point citation locator details such as page <citation>
              <biblioref linkend="Veer1996a" units="page" begin="23" end="24"/>
            </citation> and paragraph numbers.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>First and subsequent citation handling <citation>
              <biblioref linkend="Thrift1990a"/>
            </citation>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Coding for note-based citations is fully consistent with that for other citation
            classes. One need not manually place a citation in a footnote or use a special command
            like footcite to have it rendered as a note.<footnote>
              <para>... in a footnote <citation>
                  <biblioref linkend="Tilly2002a"/>
                </citation>
              </para>
            </footnote> This greatly simplifies radical style changes.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Both ibid. <citation>
              <biblioref linkend="Tilly2002a" begin="234"/>
            </citation> and complex et al. handling.<footnote>Some styles—such as APA—specify
              different et al. handling for first <citation>
                <biblioref linkend="DoeJ2002a"/>
              </citation> and subsequent <citation>
                <biblioref linkend="Brenner2000a"/>
                <biblioref linkend="DoeJ2002a"/>
              </citation> references.</footnote>
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>Configuration of author- name substitution <citation>
              <biblioref linkend="NW2000-0207"/>
              <biblioref linkend="NW2000-0424a"/>
            </citation>.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </para>
  </section>
